reviews.venue: Situated at the end of a tiny alley it's easy to miss. There's very little to it inside, a small bar and a few seats with the brewery behind. Has a good vibe as groups come in and stop off for a few beers. It's not open often so you need to plan your visit ahead.
reviews.beers: A constantly changing unapologetic yet fantastic range. Here's where you go when you want to find something unique, those new to craft beers may have trouble finding something familiar. But for those who want something new or love Belgian inspired beers you're sure to find something to tickle your fancy.
It's a fairly small range which hits all the standard favorite styles plus a few more on the adventurous side but overall it's a high quality range of beers.
reviews.venue: Situated in what seems like an old warehouse it's got that industrial feel. The corrugated iron walls tend to cause the bar to warm up significantly in the summer which gives a nice excuse to get yourself another beer.

Not what you would expect from a brewery located inside a sports club. Feels much more like an up market hipster spot. With 25 taps there's always something new on offer. If you're looking for a brewery without having to go all the way into the city then it's a good option.
reviews.beers: Most of the brewing process is done offsite with only the final fermentation being done at the actual brewery. Despite this it's a decent range, albeit a little bit safe and boring.

reviews.venue: They're currently in the process of building a new brewery in Marrickville, so no venue yet but keep a look out!
One of the original in the new wave of craft breweries Young Henry's has a big following and is often packed. Has that industrial feel that's common to breweries.
reviews.beers: A safe range which pleases the crowd it's easy to find in venues all over the country. It's decent beer but never goes past that.

reviews.venue: Rather lively and friendly brewery. Standard pallet table fixtures in a small but open space. Staff are always at hand to help with questions and provide information or even to share a beer.

location.address: 2 North Rocks Road, North Parramatta, NSW, Australia, Sydney

reviews.venue: All of the brewing is done at other friendly breweries so there's nothing like that going onsite. What they do have is a bottle shop with a fantastic range of Australian beers. It's not huge like some of the others in Sydney but if you're after a solid range of local beers then this is the place for you.
The largest of the Marrickville breweries, Batch often draws a crowd on weekends. Decorated with old couches and wooden pallets it has a very relaxed feel.
reviews.beers: Quite a few gems in an ever expanding and improving range. They'll rarely let you down
